definition: Titan (moon of Saturn), aka Saturn VI
earth/dust/clay/local/indigenous/crude opium/unsophisticated/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]
surname Wei/vassal state during the Zhou Dynasty (1066-221 BC), located in present day Henan and Hebei Provinces
to guard/to protect/to defend/abbr. for 衛生|卫生, hygiene/health/abbr. for 衛生間|卫生间, toilet

sentences.english: Are methane and ethane mixed together in hydrocarbon lakes or seas on Titan's surface?
sentences.chinese: 甲烷和乙烷是否共存於土衛六表面的湖泊或海洋中？

sentences.english: Hydrodynamic escape may have stripped Titan of much of its air, too.
sentences.chinese: 流體動力散逸可能也剝奪了土衛六的大部份大氣。

sentences.english: Today, Saturn's only massive moon is Titan.
sentences.chinese: 現如今，土衛六是土星的唯一一顆大型衛星。

sentences.english: The shadows of Titan and Mimas have both moved off the right side of the disk.
sentences.chinese: 土衛六和土衛二的影子已經移出了土星環的右邊。

sentences.english: The others are Earth and Saturn's giant moon, Titan.
sentences.chinese: 另外兩顆是地球和土衛六。

sentences.english: On Titan, methane forms clouds and maybe even rain.
sentences.chinese: 在土衛六上，甲烷可以形成雲甚至降雨。

sentences.english: Meanwhile, on Titan, it was foggy.
sentences.chinese: 與此同時，土衛六迎來的是大霧天氣。
